cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SE 

This paper deals with defending neural networks against adversarial attacks in the domain of malware classification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses various methods for training restricted networks, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with deep neural networks, which is a subfield of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions image classification, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed methods in improving classifier accuracy, which is related to cs.SE (Software Engineering).
